<taxonomicName id="3BCEEDBA640648E8B08360E14EC4ECD4" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33658" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole cerebrosior Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole cerebrosior Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerebrosior">cerebrosior</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="AE64059677E86D15C09F699232EFEC33" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181974" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole macrops Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole macrops Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrops">P. macrops</taxonomicName>
is distinguished within the complex by the following combination of traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FC1F7FC57BFD3319C8428CBF3124A9EA" type="description">
<paragraph id="B6D232AE2C7568640558825C280EF73B" pageNumber="583">Major: reddish brown; sides of pronotum longitudinally carinulate; posterior half of dorsum of head sprinkled with sparse foveae; propodeum spines relatively long and thin; apex of petiolar node in side view evenly rounded; postpetiolar node from above oval. Minor: dorsal margin of petiolar node seen from behind rises to a peak; propodeal spines vertical. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.14, HL 1.30, SL 0.60, EL 0.22, PW 0.56. Paratype minor: HW 0.52, HL 0.56, SL 0.46, EL 0.16, PW 0.30. color Major: concolorous medium reddish brown, tarsi yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D22480BC89964A3D47882304AED9F13E" pageNumber="583">Minor: body and mandibles blackish brown to black, legs and antennae medium to dark brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="002F5D5B19747C06AF90828EE3C893D5" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A9D9DD673DA35B263EE31E894B4F3ACC" pageNumber="583">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
